{"vocabInfos":[{"lsjDefs":"<b> πέπειρος</b>, ον, <br /> <b>ripe</b>, of fruit, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th-3rd c.BC: Theophrastus Philosophus “de Causis Plantarum” 3.6.9 (_comparative_), LXX.Gen.40.10, “Anthologia Graeca” 12.185 (2nd c.AD: Strato Epigrammaticus) \">LXX+4th c.BC+</a>]; of girls, opposed to νέαι, variant in [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Aristophanes Comicus “Ecclesiazusae” 896; παρθένοι 1st-2nd c.AD: Plutarchus Biographus et Philosophus “Comp. Lyc.Num.” 4, compare “Lyc.” 15; φιλέουσι πέπειρος “Anthologia Graeca” 12.9 (2nd c.AD: Strato Epigrammaticus). \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__2</b></Level3> <i>metaphorically</i>, of persons, <b>mild</b>, πεπειροτέρους γεγονότας [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 1st c.BC: Dionysius Halicarnassensis 9.49. \">Refs 1st c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__3</b></Level3> π. νοῦσος a disease <b>come to its crisis</b>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Hippocrates Medicus “περὶ διαίτης ὀξέων” 39 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; also πεπειρότερον πτύελον <b>more concocted</b>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" [prev. author] “Epid.” 2.3.4. \">Refs</a>]","strongNumber":"G8709","accentedUnicode":"πέπειρος","shortDef":"mature","mediumDef":"mature","stepGloss":"mature","stepTransliteration":"pepeiros","count":0,"_step_Type":"word"}]}